# Valuation plain English (research files)

Read **`_system/frameworks/archetype_valuation_prose.md`** and **`_system/frameworks/report_prose.md`** before writing or editing `{TICKER}/research/deep_dive_*.md` or `adversarial_*.md`.

## In narrative and Valuation & IRR sections

- Use **full words** in assumption ledger rows (see archetype guide).
- Spell out **price today**, **free cash flow per share**, **growth years 1–5**, **selling multiple in year 10**, **annual return**.
- Do **not** use `P₀`, `FCF₀`, `g1`, `g2`, `exit=25×`, `bn` without spelling out in that table.
- First mention of **IRR** in the Valuation section: **annual return at today's price**; then "IRR" is OK in Classification footer.

## Pick valuation shape from archetype

| Archetype | Method (usually) | Valuation emphasis |
|-----------|------------------|-------------------|
| compounder | ten-year cash flow | Normalized owner cash |
| croupier | ten-year cash flow | Mid-cycle normalization |
| platform | cash flow or scenarios | Volume × price → cash |
| serial_acquirer | cash flow or scenarios | Synergy timing |
| holding_co | dated payoff | Sum of the parts |
| optionality | dated payoff or scenarios | Floor + option |
| turnaround | scenarios | Bear / base / bull paths |
| infrastructure | ten-year cash flow | Yield + capital spending |

Codes (`full`, `yield_curve`) belong in footer + `valuation.json`, not as the only explanation in prose.

## Returns statement

One sentence, no abbreviations — must match executive summary base percent.
